DIr
NOTE:This suffix (except a few exceptions) follows person agreement, serves
NOTE:a number of purposes including introducing supposition, nominal
NOTE:predicates (especially in formal language). G&K calls this suffix
NOTE:'generalized modality marker', Kornfilt treats it (more or less) as a
NOTE:copula.
EX:doktor-<b>dur</b> `(supposedly) s/he is a doctor' (note that this -dur is
EX:generally not used in spoken language if supposition is not
EX:implied)
G&K:-GM
Oflazer:+Cop
Type:Verbal/cpl
